					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/faustov" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1282427); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1282427&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610250813" alt="FaustoV" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1282427)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/faustov" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1282427); return false;" >FaustoV</a></span> <span class="odate time_1435606887 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">29 Jun 2015 19:41</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2327810">
									

<p>You know, this sounds neat at first, because yeah, what's better than giving a real personality to some eldritch skips? I think this series has issues developing a proper/lkeable characterization, and HUGE plot holes.</p>
<p>First, you said the series had the porpuse to present skips as humanly as possible, but once I get to know them, I realize their personalities are flat. There's no real character development except for some few moments (and it feels forced whenever it happens). You make them look almost stereotypical. 682 is a explorer, 1129 is a super quiet and misterious character, 303 is the cotchety mad scientist, 053 is the innocent girl who will be the central engine ina group trying to look for their home and themselves, and 173 is&#8230; The Villain<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-699096-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-699096-1')">1</a></sup>&#8230;</p>
<p>As for the plot, honestly, the biggest one is about Time and Space. You are saying all of these entities are super old. Older than Universe itself, because they are survivors from a previous Universe iteration (wich is by the way, a concept that has been already explored by Marvel, but they are pretty much the comics analogue of the Simpsons, so not a big deal in my opinion). Our planet is pretty young, you know? There are many, many things that you're skipping, and unless you use the &quot;survivors got scattered in different times&quot; narrative, you're going to have a los of issues pulling this off.</p>
<div class="footnotes-footer">
<div class="title">Footnotes</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-699096-1"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-699096-1')">1</a>. And since then I cannot imagine 173 without an evil villain mustache and wearing a tall hat. If I have to deal with this from now on, I'm taking you all with me.</div>
</div>

							</div>

								
					
